{"title_page": "Rothwell (ward)", "text_new": "{{short description|Electoral ward in Leeds, England}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Use British English|date=October 2019}}\n{{infobox UK place\n| official_name     = Rothwell\n| static_image_name = Leeds UK ward map highlighting Rothwell.svg\n| static_image_caption = Rothwell highlighted within Leeds\n| metropolitan_borough = [[City of Leeds]]\n| metropolitan_county = [[West Yorkshire]]\n| shire_district =\n| lieutenancy_england =  \n| region = Yorkshire and the Humber\n| country = England\n| constituency_westminster = [[Elmet and Rothwell (UK Parliament constituency)|Elmet and Rothwell]]\n| councillor1 = Diane Chapman<ref>{{cite web | title = Councillor Diane Chapman | url = https://democracy.leeds.gov.uk/mgUserInfo.aspx?UID=7363 | website = democracy.leeds.gov.uk | publisher = [[Leeds City Council]] | access-date = 16 June 2019}}</ref><br>\n| party1      = [[Liberal Democrats (UK)|Liberal Democrats]]\n| councillor2 = Stewart Golton<ref>{{cite web | title = Councillor Stewart Golton | url = https://democracy.leeds.gov.uk/mgUserInfo.aspx?UID=244 | website = democracy.leeds.gov.uk | publisher = [[Leeds City Council]] | access-date = 30 December 2018}}</ref><br>\n| party2      = Liberal Democrats\n|councillor3 = Carmel Hall<ref>{{cite web | title = Councillor Carmel Hall | url = https://democracy.leeds.gov.uk/mgUserInfo.aspx?UID=7111 | website = democracy.leeds.gov.uk | publisher = [[Leeds City Council]] | access-date = 21 April 2020}}</ref><br>\n| party3      = Liberal Democrats\n| population     = 16,012\n| population_ref = (2019 electorate)<ref>{{cite web | title = Leeds City Council election results 2019: Rothwell | url = https://www.leeds.gov.uk/your-council/elections/leeds-city-council-election-results?ward=Rothwell | website = democracy.leeds.gov.uk | publisher = [[Leeds City Council]] | access-date = 12 May 2019}}</ref>\n| area_total_km2 = \n| area_footnotes = \n| hide_services = yes\n}}\n\n'''Rothwell''' is an electoral ward of [[Leeds City Council]] in south east [[Leeds]], [[West Yorkshire]], including the [[Rothwell, West Yorkshire|town of the same name]] and the villages of [[Carlton, Rothwell|Carlton]], [[Oulton, West Yorkshire|Oulton]] and [[Woodlesford]].\n\n== Councillors ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Election!!colspan=\"2\"|Councillor!!colspan=\"2\"|Councillor!!colspan=\"2\"|Councillor\n|-\n| [[Leeds City Council election, 1973|1973]]\n|style=\"background-color: {{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|\n|bgcolor=\"#99CCFF\"| Rose Lund ([[Labour Party (UK)|Lab]])\n|style=\"background-color: {{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|\n|bgcolor=\"#99CCFF\"| A. Benson ([[Labour Party (UK)|Lab]])\n|style=\"background-color: {{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|\n|bgcolor=\"#99CCFF\"| J. De Carieret ([[Labour Party (UK)|Lab]])\n|-\n| [[Leeds City Council election, 1975|1975]]\n|style=\"background-color: {{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|\n| Rose Lund ([[Labour Party (UK)|Lab]])\n|style=\"background-color: {{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|\n| A. Benson ([[Labour Party (UK)|Lab]])\n|style=\"background-color: {{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|\n|bgcolor=\"#99CCFF\"| S. Arran ([[Labour Party (UK)|Lab]])\n|-\n| [[Leeds City Council election, 1976|1976]]\n|style=\"background-color: {{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|\n| Rose Lund ([[Labour Party (UK)|Lab]])\n|style=\"background-color: {{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|\n|bgcolor=\"#99CCFF\"| A. Benson ([[Labour Party (UK)|Lab]])\n|style=\"background-color: {{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|\n| S. Arran ([[Labour Party (UK)|Lab]])\n|-\n| [[Leeds City Council election, 1978|1978]]\n|style=\"background-color: {{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|\n|bgcolor=\"#99CCFF\"| Rose Lund ([[Labour Party (UK)|Lab]])\n|style=\"background-color: {{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|\n| A. Benson ([[Labour Party (UK)|Lab]])\n|style=\"background-color: {{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\"|\n| S. Arran ([[Labour Party (UK)|Lab]])\n|-\n| [[Leed