19 election]], Harrison has since changed her surname to Hall.}}\n|style=\"background-color: {{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}}\"|\n| Stewart Golton* ([[Liberal Democrats (UK)|LD]])\n|style=\"background-color: {{Liberal Democrats (UK)/meta/color}}\"|\n|bgcolor=\"#99CCFF\"| Diane Chapman* ([[Liberal Democrats (UK)|LD]])\n|}\n{{Color box|#99CCFF|border=darkgray}} indicates seat up for re-election.\n''*'' indicates incumbent councillor.\n\n== Elections since 2010 ==\n===May 2019===\n{{Election box begin |title=[[2019 Leeds City Council election|2019]]}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Liberal Democrats (UK)\n  |candidate  = Diane Chapman\n  |votes      = 2,206\n  |percentage = 42.0\n  |change     = -2.6\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Labour Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Karen Bruce*\n  |votes      = 1,731\n  |percentage = 32.9\n  |change     = +0.2\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Conservative Party (UK)\n  |candidate  = Joe Boycott\n  |votes      = 623\n  |percentage = 11.9\n  |change     = -5.7\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = For Britain Movement\n  |candidate  = Simon Michael Crowe\n  |votes      = 409\n  |percentage = 7.8\n  |change     = +7.8\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Green Party of England and Wales\n  |candidate  = Ali Aliremzioglu\n  |votes      = 288\n  |percentage = 5.5\n  |change     = +0.5\n}}\n{{Election box majority|\n  |votes      = 475\n  |percentage = 9.1\n  |change     = -4.5\n}}\n{{Election box turnout|\n  |votes      = 5,306\n  |percentage = 33.1\n  |change     = -4.6\n}}\n{{Election box gain with party link|\n |winner     = Liberal Democrats (UK)\n |loser      = Labour Party (UK)\n |swing      = -1.4\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n===May 2018===\n{{Election box begin |title=[[Leeds City Council election, 2018|2018]]}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link|\n  |party     